						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">Śaka 1435 (1513 A.D.)</hi></p>						

						<p>Partly built in and damaged. Registers the gift of a grove (<hi rend="italic">tōppu</hi>) 900 <hi rend="italic">kuḻi</hi> in extent, by Timmappa-nāyakkar and Ādiyappa-nāyakkar, sons of <hi rend="bold">Vasa-</hi> vaśaṅkara Mallappa-nāyakkar, the <hi rend="italic">Vāśal</hi> officer of Kṛishṇadēvarāyar. Mentions also Chinnappa-nāyakkar along with the other two as a donor. The details of the date viz. <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1435, Śrīmukha, ••••• ba. 5, Monday, Uttiram</hi> are incomplete and also irregular. <hi rend="bold">1435, Śrimukha corresponds to 1513 A.D.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
